description.plain: YK Osiris first went viral after uploading snippets of his song “Timing” on Instagram, which got re-posted by the media outlet SayCheeseTV. He later followed up with his hit singles “I’m Next (Freestyle)” and “Valentine,” the latter of which has earned more than 30 million YouTube views. The Kiwi-produced track is inspired by the young rapper’s experience with heartbreak on YouTube.

songs.title: Valentine

description.plain: “Valentine” is a song by American singer YK Osiris, released on May 14, 2018 by Universal Music Group. It served as the first single from his debut studio album, The Golden Child. The single didn’t chart as well in 2018. The song was released on October 31, 2019 and has been Certified Platinum by Recording Industry Association of America.

songs.title: Worth It

description.plain: This song talks about how YK Osiris loves his girl so much that he’ll give her absolutely whatever she wants as long as she’s good to him. He also doesn’t care about any unimportant stuff. He doesn’t care about how much makeup she has or about her curves, he just cares that she has the best personality. And as long as she has that, she’s perfect in his eyes and he’ll treat her like a queen.
